Chain_Info1_Token_Description1="<a href='https://github.com/godwokenrises/godwoken/blob/develop/docs/life_of_a_polyjuice_transaction.md#pckb' class='a-config' target='_blank'>pCKB</a> is an erc20 representation of CKB on L2. Deployed on the Godwoken chain, it is the new concept that Godwoken v1 introduced, and its value is pegged to Nervos' native token (CKByte or CKB). This means the value of pCKB is the same as the value of CKB. pCKB’s role on Godwoken is similar to that of ETH’s role on Ethereum where it is used to collect transaction fees, and even allows developers and users to claim storage space on the Nervos blockchain in proportion to their holdings. <br><br>While different Godwoken chains may use different token types as pCKB, the Godwoken chain uses CKB as pCKB by default, pCKB, as the unit for calculating transaction fees in Godwoken, has a similar calculating method for transaction fees to that of Ethereum. Click <a href='https://docs.godwoken.io/fastWithdrawal' class='a-config' target='_blank'>here</a> for more information about pCKB."



